<item>
            <title>[SOLR-781] Change facet.sort from boolean to string and specify sort method explicitely</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-781</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The facet.sort parameter is currently a boolean, which has some downsides as explained in &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/facet.sort-parameter-td19570834.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/facet.sort-parameter-td19570834.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Changing it to a string which explicitely states the sort method would address these issues.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12404791">SOLR-781</key>
            <summary>Change facet.sort from boolean to string and specify sort method explicitely</summary>
                <type id="2" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/newfeature.png">New Feature</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.png">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
